### Q4. find the average number of cases month-wise in dataset and arrange them starting from Jan to Dec (you may use month.name built-in constant for same)

#### (a) using base R and barplot function (first convert the cumulative Confirmed column to per day Confirmed col using diff function)

    df <- with(covid, aggregate(Confirmed, by = list(date(DT)), sum))
    colnames(df) <- c('Date', 'Cumulative Cases')
    df$Cases <- c(df$`Cumulative Cases`[1], diff(df$`Cumulative Cases`))
    df$Year <- year(df$Date)
    df$Month <- month(df$Date, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE)
    df_ma <- with(df, aggregate(Cases, by = list(Year, Month), mean))
    rm(df)
    colnames(df_ma) <- c("Year", "Month", "Average Cases")
    df_ma$`Average Cases` <- round(df_ma$`Average Cases`, 0)
    df_ma <- rbind(df_ma[df_ma$Year == 2020,], df_ma[df_ma$Year == 2021,])
    barplot(xtabs(`Average Cases`~Year + Month, df_ma) -> tab,
            las = 2, beside = TRUE, col = c('green','red'),
            main = "Monthwise Average Cases")
    legend('topright', legend = c(2020,2021), fill = c('green','red'), cex = 0.5)

    # Radial plot: Average number of cases month-wise
    df1 |> 
      group_by(month) |> 
      summarise(avg_conf = mean(per_day_case)) |> 
      ggplot(aes(x = factor(month), y = avg_conf, fill = month)) +
      geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
      coord_polar() +
      scale_fill_brewer(palette = 'Paired') +
      labs(title = "Month wise average number of cases",
           subtitle = "",
           x = "Year", y = "Average Confirmed Case", fill = "Month") +
      theme(axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
            axis.text.y = element_blank(), 
            axis.text.x = element_text(face = 'bold'),
            plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
            legend.position = 'none')

### Q5. visualize the number of confirmed cases year wise but months stacked (use format command to extract the year component or some other suitable technique before proceeding)

    df1 |> 
      group_by(year, month) |> 
      summarise(sum_conf = sum(per_day_case), .groups = 'drop_last') |> 
      ggplot(aes(x = factor(year), y = sum_conf, fill = month)) +
      geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = 'stack') +
      scale_fill_brewer(palette = 'Paired') +
      scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,2e+07,5e+06), labels = c(0,paste(seq(5,20,5),'M'))) +
      labs(title = "Stacked bar chart of confirmed case",
           subtitle = "(The number of confirmed cases year wise but months stacked)",
           caption = '*Confirmed cases in (M) Million scale',
           x = "Year", y = "Confirmed Case", fill = "Month") +
      theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
            plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

### Q6. find state-wise the extremes in highs and lows (i.e. the largest fluctuation) in terms of cured, deaths and plot the same using ggplot

    df2 <- covid |>
      mutate(year = year(DT), month = month(DT, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE), day = day(DT)) |> 
      group_by(`State/UnionTerritory`) |> 
      mutate(cured_per_day = c(Cured[1],diff(Cured)),
             deaths_per_day = c(Deaths[1],diff(Deaths))) |> 
      select(c(1,6,7,8,9,10))
    df2 |> 
      filter(cured_per_day < 50000 & deaths_per_day < 1500) |> 
      gather(key = 'cd', value = 'cd_per_day', 5:6) |> 
      ggplot(aes(x = `State/UnionTerritory`, y = cd_per_day, fill = cd)) + 
      geom_boxplot() +
      facet_wrap(~factor(cd, labels = c("Cured","Death")), scales = "free_y") +
      labs(y = '', title = "Per day state-wise fluctuation in terms of cured and deaths") +
      scale_fill_discrete(name = 'Per day statistics', labels = c('Cured', 'Deaths')) +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0))

### Q13. plot the fluctuations of per day confirmed cases statewise, order by amount of fluctuations (Hint: use IQR) hint: use boxplot

    covid |> 
      group_by(`State/UnionTerritory`) |> 
      summarise(per_day_conf = c(Confirmed[1], diff(Confirmed)), .groups = 'drop_last') |> 
      ungroup() |> 
      filter(per_day_conf > 0) |> 
      ggplot(aes(x = reorder(`State/UnionTerritory`, -per_day_conf), y = per_day_conf)) +
      geom_boxplot() +
      labs(x = 'State/Union Territory', y = 'Per day confirmed case',
           title = "Statewise Fluctuation of Per Day Confirmed Cases") +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0),

### Q14. create a fluctuations (IQR) based 4 categories and plot them using geom\_jitter

    covid |>
      group_by(Date = as.Date(DT)) |> 
      summarise(cum_conf = sum(Confirmed),
                cum_cured = sum(Cured),
                cum_deaths = sum(Deaths), .groups = 'drop_last') |> 
      ungroup() |> 
      mutate(per_day_conf = c(cum_conf[1], diff(cum_conf)),
             per_day_deaths = c(cum_deaths[1], diff(cum_deaths)),
             per_day_cured = c(cum_cured[1], diff(cum_cured)),
             per_day_active = per_day_conf - (per_day_cured + per_day_deaths)) |> 
      select(-c(2,3,4)) |> 
      gather(key = 'cdc', value = 'per_day_value', 2:5) |>
      filter(per_day_value > 0 & per_day_value < 4e+05) |>
      ggplot(aes(x = reorder(cdc, -per_day_value), y = per_day_value, col = factor(cdc))) + 
      geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, coef = 0) + geom_jitter(width = 0.1) + 
      scale_color_discrete(labels = c('Active', 'Confirmed', 'Cured', 'Deaths')) +
      scale_x_discrete(labels = c('Cured', 'Confirmed', 'Active', 'Death')) +
      labs(x = "Type of case", y = "Per day count",
           title = "Fluctuation based on type of cases", col = "Case Type")

### Q16. find the relationship between deaths per day, confirmed per day, cured per day in a time series plot

    covid |>
      group_by(Date = as.Date(DT)) |> 
      summarise(cum_conf = sum(Confirmed),
                cum_cured = sum(Cured),
                cum_deaths = sum(Deaths), .groups = 'drop_last') |> 
      ungroup() |> 
      mutate(per_day_conf = c(cum_conf[1], diff(cum_conf)),
             per_day_deaths = c(cum_deaths[1], diff(cum_deaths)),
             per_day_cured = c(cum_cured[1], diff(cum_cured))) |> 
      select(-c(2,3,4)) |> 
      gather(key = 'cdc', value = 'per_day_value', 2:4) |>
      filter(per_day_value > 0 & per_day_value < 2e+06) |> 
      ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = per_day_value, col = cdc)) +
      geom_line(size = 1, alpha = 0.8) +
      labs(y = "Per day count",
           title = "Line chart of per day confirmed, cured and death case",
           color = "Case Type",
           caption = '*(Per day count in (L) Lakh)') +
      scale_x_date(date_labels = format("%Y-%b"), date_breaks = '1 month') +
      scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,800000,100000), labels = c(0, paste(1:8, 'L'))) +
      scale_color_manual(values = c('blue','green','red'),
                         labels = c('Confirmed','Cured','Deaths')) +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, hjust = 1),
            legend.position = 'top',
            plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = 'bold'))
